                      <span>3</span>
                      votes <span class="ItemCaption">Reviewed: </span>
                      <span>1998-10-15</span>
                    </div>
                    <span>Starting with Hackenbush (thanks to Groucho Marx) this book describes and  analyzes a great many interesting games.  While the authors are  mathematicians, and there is mathematics involved,  much of the discussion  can be followed by the lay reader.</span>
                  
              
